 2005 award due to [[University of Southern California athletics scandal|NCAA violations]]).\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=9 style=\"{{NCAA color cell|Notre Dame Fighting Irish}};\"| Heisman Trophy Winners\n|-\n{{CollegePrimaryHeader|team=Notre Dame Fighting Irish|Year|Name|Position}}\n|-\n| 1943 || [[Angelo Bertelli]] || QB \n|-\n| 1947 || [[Johnny Lujack]] || QB \n|-\n| 1949 || [[Leon Hart]] || End \n|-\n| 1953 || [[Johnny Lattner]] || HB \n|-\n| 1956 || [[Paul Hornung]] || OB \n|-\n| 1964 || [[John Huarte]] || QB \n|-\n| 1987 || [[Tim Brown (American football)|Tim Brown]] || WR  \n|}\n\n'''Heisman voting:'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/archive/nd-m-footbl-archive.html/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=December 30, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081217101247/http://und.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/archive/nd-m-footbl-archive.html |archivedate=December 17, 2008 |df=mdy }}</ref>\n{{colbegin}}\n*1938 \u2013 Whitney Beinor, 9th\n*1943 \u2013 '''[[Angelo Bertelli]], 1st''', [[Creighton Miller]], 4th, Jim White, 9th\n*1944 \u2013 [[Bob Kelly (American football)|Bob Kelly]], 6th\n*1945 \u2013 [[Frank Dancewicz]], 6th\n*1946 - [[Johnny Lujack]], 3rd \n*1947 \u2013 '''[[Johnny Lujack]], 1st'''\n*1949 \u2013 '''[[Leon Hart]], 1st''', [[Bob Williams (quarterback)|Bob Williams]], 5th, [[Emil Sitko]], 8th\n*1950 \u2013 [[Bob Williams (quarterback)|Bob Williams]], 6th\n*1953 \u2013 '''[[Johnny Lattner]], 1st'''\n*1954 \u2013 [[Ralph Guglielmi]], 4th\n*1956 \u2013 '''[[Paul Hornung]], 1st'''\n*1958 \u2013 [[Nick Pietrosante]], 10th\n*1959 \u2013 [[Monty Stickles]], 9th\n*1964 \u2013 '''[[John Huarte]], 1st''', [[Jack Snow (American football)|Jack Snow]], 5th\n*1965 \u2013 Bill Wolski, 11th\n*1966 \u2013 [[Nick Eddy]], 3rd, [[Terry Hanratty]], 6th\n*1967 \u2013 [[Terry Hanratty]], 9th\n*1968 \u2013 [[Terry Hanratty]], 3rd\n*1969 \u2013 [[Mike McCoy (defensive tackle)|Mike McCoy]], 6th\n*1970 \u2013 [[Joe Theismann]], 2